1) Written 16 bit bootloader
2) Used Qemu to loead the kernel
3) In real mode, 16 bit can be accessed. 1MB memory is available. In real mode, there is no memory securtiy and no hardware security.
4) kernel area is ring0 and user are is ring 3
5) What are segment registers.
a) Code Segment
b) Stack Segment
c) Data Segment
d) Extra Segment
6) Implemented vector interrupt table: You do not call it through function call. You call it by number.
Q:- What is an interrupt ?
A:- a) Processor is interrupted b) old state is saved on stack c) interrupt executed

7) Read from the disk in real mode
8) Protection Mode:- Protection Mode allows you to protect memory from hardware talking to memory. There are various rings in protection mode.
RING -0 ==> Kernel
RING-3 ===> User applications
Protection mode gives access to 4 gb of memory. while real mode give 1 MB of memory.

9) implemented GDT, GDT describes various memory segents. descriptors are 8 bytes. Describe size/access right of that memory segment.
10) segent registers hold Segment selctors. Each segment selector is 2 byte. segment selector corresponds to the descriptors in GDT.
A segment selector is a 16-bit value that identifies a specific segment by pointing to an entry in a descriptor table (the GDT or LDT). 
It's what gets loaded into a segment register — the segment register doesn't hold the segment's properties directly, just this "pointer" to where those properties are described.
